  Saudi Arabia’s ambassador to Nigeria, Mr Adnan Mahmoud Bostaji, has passed away. A statement by the Royal Embassy of Saudi Arabia on Tuesday confirmed the news. The statement reads, “With the deepest sense of sadness and complete submission to the will of Allah, Royal Embassy announces the passing away of His Excellency, the Ambassador of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to Nigeria, Mr Adnan Mahmoud Bostaji. May his blessed soul rest in peace.”